{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01EHCrPwN8TngFxr3Q6c78g1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me break down this request:\n\n1. Generate 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files\n2. Save to tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.21.txt\n3. Filenames must use SPACES, not hyphens/underscores\n4. Preserve Polish diacritics in filenames\n5. Filename title must match content title (case-insensitive OK)\n\nRecipe mix:\n- ~60% English (~6 recipes)\n- ~40% Polish (~4 recipes)\n- Variety of categories\n- Multi-word titles (2-5 words) and single-word\n\nPattern requirements:\n- 5 files with MULTILANG (Polish + English + optional 3rd script)\n- 3 files with COMPOUND (multiple recipes/variations in title)\n- 2 files with SIMPLE (basic OCR noise, stray numbers, page headers)\n\nFile length: 15-60 lines (longer ones 40-60)\n\nI need to avoid recipes that already exist in the list provided.\n\nLet me plan 10 recipes:\n\nMULTILANG (5 files) - mix of Polish and English:\n1. Szarlotka z Jabłkami / Apple Cake with Cream - Polish/English\n2. Żurawina z Miodem / Cranberry Honey Jam - Polish/English\n3. Placki Trawie / Herb Pancakes - Polish/English\n4. Łazanki z Mąką / Egg Noodles - Polish/English\n5. Żabka w Liściach / Frog Legs Wrapped - Polish/English\n\nCOMPOUND (3 files) - multiple recipes/variations:\n6. MUSHROOM BREAD WITH SEEDS : MUSHROOM BREAD WITH HERBS\n7. POLISH SOURDOUGH RYE + POLISH SOURDOUGH WHEAT\n8. BAKED FISH WITH HERBS : FISH WITH CAPERS (VARIATION)\n\n\n9. Simple English/Polish soup with OCR errors\n10. Simple English recipe with OCR noise\n\nNow I'll generate the actual recipes with realistic OCR artifacts like broken words, page numbers, stray numbers, and partial line breaks. I'll start with the multilang recipes, then compound variations, finishing with the simple ones that have more OCR noise and formatting issues.\n\n**Szarlotka z Jabłkami / Apple Cake with Cream** (MULTILANG, 40 lines) - a traditional Polish apple cake with standard formatting and OCR noise mixed in.\n\n**Żurawina z Miodem / Cranberry Honey Jam** (MULTILANG, 35 lines) - Polish jam recipe with English variant. **Placki Trawie / Herb Pancakes** (MULTILANG, 30 lines) - Polish herb pancakes. **Łazanki z Mąką / Egg Noodles** (MULTILANG, 28 lines) - Polish egg noodles. **Pstrąg Pieczony / Roasted Trout** (MULTILANG, 35 lines) - a more realistic Polish fish dish instead of the frog legs option. These multilang recipes will have moderate OCR noise, then I'll create the compound variations with more artifacts, and finish with the simple recipes that have heavier OCR degradation. I need to cross-reference against what's already catalogued. Looking at the existing entries, I see several żurek variations and żurawina preparations are already documented. Szarlotka's also in there, so I should remove that from consideration. Let me map out what's actually present: żurek with multiple regional and ingredient variations, żurawina kompot with nuts, żur with potatoes, and several zupy including szczawiowa and cebulowa. A few like zupa jarzynowa and zupa pomidorowa aren't yet included, which opens up space for those instead. -Fried Smoked Cheese. I'm settling on more accessible options: Żabka Pieczona with roasted frog legs, Grzyby Marynowane for marinated mushrooms, Oscypek Smażony as pan-fried smoked cheese, Chleb Żytni for rye bread, and Karp Pieczony featuring roasted carp with almonds. These span roughly 28-40 lines each. Now I need to work through the compound recipes.\n\nFor the paired variations, I'm looking at wild mushroom soup with two versions—one with barley and one with beans at around 50 lines. Polish cabbage rolls work well as a traditional-modern pairing at 45 lines. Herb roasted pork chops with an apple sauce variation gives me another 42-line compound entry. Then for simpler recipes, I'll include a lentil and vegetable soup with some OCR noise, and swap out the duplicate mushroom soup for a mushroom cream version instead.\n\nActually, I need to verify what's already in the collection. Zupa Pieczarkowa, Zupa Pomidorowa, and Zupa Grzybowa are all present, so I should use Zupa Jarzynowa with dumplings as my second simple recipe to avoid redundancy. For the multilingual files, I'll structure them with Polish on the first line, English translation on the second, and occasionally a third variant. The compound files will have the paired title at the top. I'll incorporate OCR artifacts naturally throughout to simulate scanned document imperfections, then generate all ten files with realistic recipe content.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16778,"cache_read_input_tokens":65286,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16778},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"39fa0393-55f5-48c6-9ef5-33cf17b4d5f5","uuid":"9910a8b5-0934-4579-86c1-93f1e804a60b"}
