{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01EHCrPwN8TngFxr3Q6c78g1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012ubSnLsgwKZKGciz8G8dKA","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Żabka Pieczona.generated.21.txt","content":"Żabka Pieczona\nRoasted Frog Legs with Thyme\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n- 2 pairs fresh frog legs, cleaned\n- 4 tbsp butter, divided\n- 8 cloves garlic, minced\n- 3 tbsp fresh thyme leaves\n- 2 tbsp fresh parsley, chopped\n- 1/2 cup white wine\n- Salt and black pepper to taste\n- 2 tbsp lemon juice\n- 1 tbsp flour for dusting\n\nPREPARATION:\n\nPat frog legs dry with paper towels. Season generously with salt and pepper on both\nsides. Dust lightly with flour.\n\nHeat 2 tbsp of butter in a large cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat. When foam\nsubsides, carefully place frog legs in pan. Cook 4-5 minutes per side until golden brown,\nturning carefully.\n\nRemove legs to a warm plate. In same skillet, reduce heat to medium and add remaining\nbutter. Add minced garlic and fresh thyme leaves, stirring constantly for 1 minute until\nfragrant.\n\nPour in white wine, scraping up any brown bits stuck to bottom. Return frog legs to pan,\ntucking fresh parsley around them. Squeeze lemon juice over top.\n\nCover with foil and roast in 375°F oven for 8-10 minutes. Baste once with pan juices.\n\nServe hot with pan sauce spooned over top. Accompaniment: crusty bread or roasted potatoes.\n\nNOTES:\nTraditional French-Polish preparation. Frog legs have delicate, mild flavor similar to\nchicken. Always source from reputable butcher or specialty food purveyor. Serves 2-3.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16778,"cache_read_input_tokens":65286,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16778},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier