{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_018GSkZyn7zThop7eHYoa16j","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019w2WUoQ4DWNSTnroEGwMi1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/POLISH CABBAGE ROLLS TRADITIONAL + POLISH CABBAGE ROLLS MODERN.generated.21.txt","content":"POLISH CABBAGE ROLLS TRADITIONAL + POLISH CABBAGE ROLLS MODERN\n\nVERSION 1 - TRADITIONAL GOLABKI WITH PORK AND RICE\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n- 1 large head green cabbage\n- 400g ground pork\n- 150g ground beef\n- 1 cup cooked short-grain rice\n- 1 large onion, finely diced\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 egg, beaten\n- 2 tbsp fresh parsley\n- 1 tbsp tomato paste\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 cups tomato sauce\n- 1 cup beef stock\n- 2 tbsp sour cream\n\nPREPARATION:\nCarefully peel leaves from cabbage. Blanch leaves in boiling salted water 3-4 minutes\nuntil pliable. Drain on paper towels.\n\nMix pork, beef, rice, sautéed onion and garlic, egg, parsley, tomato paste, salt,\npepper. Lay cabbage leaf, place ~3 tbsp filling at base, tuck sides and roll tightly.\n\nArrange seam-side down in baking dish. Combine tomato sauce and stock, pour over rolls.\nCover with foil, bake at 350°F for 45 minutes. Remove foil, bake additional 15 minutes.\n\nFinish with dollop sour cream. Serves 6.\n\n---\n\nVERSION 2 - MODERN GOLABKI WITH TURKEY, QUINOA & HERBS\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n- 1 large head green cabbage\n- 500g ground turkey (ground chicken works too)\n- 1.5 cups cooked quinoa\n- 1 red bell pepper, finely diced\n- 2 shallots, minced\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tbsp fresh herbs (parsley, dill, oregano)\n- 1/2 cup grated zucchini (squeezed dry)\n- 1 egg\n- Salt, pepper, cayenne to taste\n- 1.5 cups tomato sauce\n- 1 cup vegetable stock\n- Greek yogurt for serving\n- Microgreens for garnish\n\nPREPARATION:\nPrepare cabbage leaves as above. Combine turkey, quinoa, bell pepper, shallots, garlic,\nfresh herbs, zucchini, egg, seasonings.\n\nAssemble rolls as in traditional version. Arrange in baking dish, combine tomato sauce\nwith stock, pour over. Cover and bake 40 minutes at 375°F, uncover and bake 10 more.\n\nServe with dollop Greek yogurt and fresh microgreens. Lighter, more contemporary version\nwhile honoring classic preparation. Serves 6.\n\nNOTES: Both versions freeze beautifully before or after cooking. Traditional served\nduring family gatherings, modern version gaining popularity among health-conscious cooks.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":814,"cache_read_input_tokens":87628,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":814},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"39fa0393-55f5-48c6-9ef5-33cf17b4d5f5","uuid":"0526a2e7-3679-43c6-af8e-fd324c1afe18"}
