{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_013WNcXDJSUjZXGXrAM3E1So","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ExCZ9oLE35i3JAeBgs27t1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/HERB ROASTED PORK CHOPS : PORK CHOPS WITH APPLE SAUCE (VARIATION).generated.21.txt","content":"HERB ROASTED PORK CHOPS : PORK CHOPS WITH APPLE SAUCE (VARIATION)\n\nBASE RECIPE - HERB ROASTED PORK CHOPS\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n- 4 pork chops (1.5 inches thick, bone-in preferred)\n- 4 tbsp butter, softened\n- 3 tbsp fresh herb blend (rosemary, thyme, sage, parsley)\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- Zest of 1 lemon\n- Salt and black pepper\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1/2 cup dry white wine\n\nPREPARATION:\nCombine softened butter, fresh herbs, minced garlic, lemon zest. Season generously with\nsalt and pepper. Massage herb butter all over pork chops, especially into bone.\n\nLet chops come to room temperature, 15-20 minutes. Heat olive oil in large cast-iron\nskillet over medium-high heat until shimmering.\n\nSear chops 4-5 minutes per side until golden brown crust develops. Pour white wine into\npan, reduce heat to medium. Transfer skillet to 375°F oven.\n\nRoast 8-12 minutes depending on thickness, until internal temperature reaches 145°F.\nRest 5 minutes before serving. Serves 4.\n\n---\n\nVARIATION - PORK CHOPS WITH APPLE SAUCE\n\nAPPLE SAUCE COMPONENT:\n- 4 medium apples (Granny Smith or mixed), peeled, cored, sliced\n- 2 tbsp butter\n- 1/4 cup apple cider vinegar\n- 2 tbsp honey or brown sugar\n- 1 cinnamon stick\n- 3-4 whole cloves\n- 1/4 tsp nutmeg\n- Salt to taste\n\nPREPARATION OF APPLE SAUCE:\nMelt butter, add apple slices and cook over medium heat 3-4 minutes until softened.\nAdd vinegar, honey, cinnamon stick, cloves, nutmeg. Simmer uncovered 15 minutes,\nstirring occasionally, until apples break down into chunky sauce.\n\nPress through food mill for smoother texture, or leave chunky. Season with salt.\n\nASSEMBLY:\nPrepare herb roasted pork chops as in base recipe. Top each chop with generous spoonful\nwarm apple sauce, garnish with fresh thyme sprig.\n\nSERVING SUGGESTION:\nServe with roasted root vegetables or crushed potato puree. Apple sauce provides sweet-\ntart complement to savory herb-roasted pork. Serves 4.\n\nNOTES: Apple sauce can be made ahead and reheated. Base herb preparation works equally\nwell with chicken breast or veal chops. Variation popular in Central European cuisine.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":902,"cache_read_input_tokens":88442,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":902},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"39fa0393-55f5-48c6-9ef5-33cf17b4d5f5","uuid":"48e77251-1497-44c8-b81c-f0f8c84bfa17"}
