{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01WdU6DYUGCSPvUbsbUYPmjU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011XhDYPqs8t2EJj5jZPyGpN","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Zupa Jarzynowa z Kluskami.generated.21.txt","content":"Zupa Jarzynowa z Kluskami\n(Vegetable Soup with Dumplings)\n\nCZĘŚĆ 1: ZUPA / PART 1: SOUP BASE\n\nSKŁADNIKI / INGREDIENTS:\n- 2 tbsp butter or sunflower oil\n- 1 large  onion, diced finely\n- 3  carrots, sliced thin (approximately  0.5 cm thickness)\n- 2 parsnips, diced\n- 1 small celeriac root, peeled, cubed (important!)\n- 3 medium potatoes (waxy variety preferre\n- 6 cups vegetable or light chicken  broth / stock\n- 2 bay leaves\n- 4-5 fresh thyme sprigs\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 1 tbsp fresh dill, chopped fine\n- Squeeze of lemon juice (optional, ~89 adds brightness)\n\nPRZYGOTOWANIE / PREPARATION:\n\nHeat butter in large pot over medium heat. Add diced onion, cook stirring until\ngolden and soft (6-8 minutes is ideal – not brown, golden).\n\nAdd carrots, parsnips, celeriac. Stir well with wooden spoon, coating vegetables\nin butter. Cook 5 minutes uncovered. Aroma will develop. This step essential for\nflavor development12 in final soup.\n\nAdd diced potatoes and broth. Drop in bay leaves and thyme sprigs. Bring mixture\nto boil, then reduce immediately to gentle simmer.\n\nCook uncovered 25-30 minutes until all vegetables tender when pierced with fork.\nSeason with salt, pepper. Remove bay leaves. Stir in fresh dill and optional lemon.\n\n---\n\nCZĘŚĆ 2: KLUSKI / PART 2: DUMPLINGS\n\nSKŁADNIKI / INGREDIENTS FOR DUMPLINGS:\n- 2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 egg, room temperature\n- 1/2 tsp salt\n- 4 tbsp cold butter, cubed\n- Approximately 6-7 tbsp lukewarm water  (add gradually – 6 exact)\n- Pinch nutmeg (optional)\n\nPRZYGOTOWANIE / PREPARATION:\n\nIn bowl, mix flour and salt. Make well in center. Drop in cubed butter and\negg. Using fork, incorporate flour gradually into wet ingredients.\n\nAdd water slowly, one tablespoon at time. Dough should be soft but not sticky.\nForm into ball, wrap in plastic, rest 15 minutes minimum.\n\nBring soup to gentle simmer. Using two spoons, drop small dumplings (teaspoon-size)\ndirectly into simmering soup. They will sink, then rise to surface when cooked.\n\nContinue adding dumplings in batches. Simmer 10 minutes total after last dumpling\nadded. Dumplings should be fluffy, light (never heavy or dense – indicates overworking).\n\nServe hot with fresh dill garnish. Traditional Polish comfort soup served year-round.\n\nNOTES: Zupa Jarzynowa signature Polish dish. Proportions flexible  – adjust vegetables\nbased on availability & season. Dumplings can be made ahead (stored in refrigerator).\nServes 6-8.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":878,"cache_read_input_tokens":90226,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":878},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"39fa0393-55f5-48c6-9ef5-33cf17b4d5f5","uuid":"18229226-e07e-4d13-a910-4a3281bf39d1"}
